    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Usage and Perception of Consumers towards Milk Products With Reference To Shreeji Milk Foods Pvt.Ltd</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Venkateswararao Battini</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Usage and Perception<br />Milk Products</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2010 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P4757</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The project is about consumer perception towards dairy products with special reference to Shreeji milk foods pvt.ltd, Chennai. This brings the information culled from various sources, it includes different sources of delectable Indian milk delicious products like milk sweets, ice creams, kulfi etc., and it gives the information from different regions of the country. 
From the ancient time onwards, India is popular for preparing a wide variety of milk delicious. It is an unending process, an array of sweets are made from different regions of the country. The milkâ€™s perishable taste has overcome. The processing aim is to extend the shelf life of milk. Thus the various diverse methods has been developed to prepare as well as to preserve milk. 50-55% of milk produced in India is converted into variety of milk products, using some processes such as coagulation, desiccation, fermentation etc., 
Even though 46% of the milk produced is consumed as liquid milk, its consumption can be stimulated. Milk plays an important role in national diet as well as in day today life. In households, the milk is preserved for 24 hours by repeated boiling, also it is soured by adding lactic contents to it, which brings an acid taste, particularly in hot climate and called as buttermilk.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8324">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8324</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/8042">MBA-2010</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
